  "text": "Colorectal cancer is the third most common cancer in men and the second in women, with 1,360,000 new cases diagnosed per year worldwide [CITATION_1] . Surgery is the main curative option in stage I-III and may often prevent cancer-related complications in stage IV. Colorectal cancer most frequently occurs in the elderly: at the time of diagnosis 60% of patients are over the age of 70, and 43% are over 75 [CITATION_2] .",
